## Order [/orders/{ID}]
An order has a recipient (ID), the date when it was placed, an ETA, ATA, status (placed, dispatched, delivered, failed) and the order detail which contains an array of item IDs and quantities.

+ Parameters

    + ID: "1234" (string) - the order ID

### Retrieve Order [GET]
Retrieve a single order

+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        {
            "ID": "1234",
            "recipientID": "1000",
            "placed": "2017-09-07T20:41:45Z",
            "estimatedTimeArrival": "2017-09-07T23:30:00Z",
            "actualTimeArrival": "",
            "status": "dispatched",
            "detail": [
                {"itemID": "2", "quantity": 3},
                {"itemID": "4", "quantity": 1},
                {"itemID": "6", "quantity": 1},
                {"itemID": "7", "quantity": 1}               
            ]
        }
 
## Orders Collection [/orders]
Orders

### Place a new Order [POST]
Place an order to be delivered. The request body must have a recipient ID and the order detail, an array of items IDs and quntities.
A succesful order will return a 201 status and the full order body.

+ Request (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        {
            "recipientID": "1000",
            "detail": [
                {"itemID": "2", "quantity": 3},
                {"itemID": "4", "quantity": 1},
                {"itemID": "6", "quantity": 1},
                {"itemID": "7", "quantity": 1}               
            ]
        }


+ Response 201 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        {
            "ID": "1234",
            "recipientID": "1000",
            "placed": "2017-09-07T20:41:45Z",
            "estimatedTimeArrival": "2017-09-07T23:30:00Z",
            "actualTimeArrival": "",
            "status": "placed",
            "detail": [
                {"itemID": "2", "quantity": 3},
                {"itemID": "4", "quantity": 1},
                {"itemID": "6", "quantity": 1},
                {"itemID": "7", "quantity": 1}               
            ]
        }

